  <h1>CBZ Semester 1 Important Questions & Answers (2025)</h1>  <section>
    <h2 class="subject-title">üåø BOTANY</h2>
    <h3>Long Answer Examples:</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>*Spirogyra*:</strong> Structure includes spiral chloroplasts; reproduces via fragmentation and conjugation forming zygospores.</li>
      <li><strong>*Funaria*:</strong> Shows alternation of generations; dominant gametophyte and dependent sporophyte.</li>
      <li><strong>*Chara*:</strong> Complex green algae; helps in water purification and compost formation.</li>
    </ul>
    <h3>Short Answer Examples:</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Alternation of generations:</strong> Alternating gametophyte and sporophyte phases.</li>
      <li><strong>Isogamy:</strong> Fusion of similar gametes.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>  <section>
    <h2 class="subject-title">üêü ZOOLOGY</h2>
    <h3>Long Answer Examples:</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Canal system in *Sycon*:</strong> Water flow system with ostia and osculum for nutrient intake.</li>
      <li><strong>*Ascaris*:</strong> Cylindrical parasitic worm with pseudocoelom and complete digestive tract.</li>
      <li><strong>*Hydra*:</strong> Reproduces sexually and asexually via budding.</li>
    </ul>
    <h3>Short Answer Examples:</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Radial symmetry:</strong> Body divided into equal halves from any angle (e.g., starfish).</li>
      <li><strong>Metamerism:</strong> Body segmentation (e.g., earthworm).</li>
    </ul>
  </section>  <section>
